org.fhnw.aigs.commons

Class Player

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fhnw.aigs.commons.Player

  • public class Player
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the Player. A player has a name and a unique id which is not to be confused with the ID the player can have inside a game. For every game, there must be a new player. This means that one player cannot be in two games. Therefore a new connection must be established for every new game. This is why it is possible to identify every player by his or her socket. This socket can be used to send messages.
